<section class="about" id="about">
  <div class="section-label"><span>About me</span></div>
  <div class="about-grid">
    <div class="about-text reveal">
      <p>I graduated from UCF with a <strong>BS in Finance</strong> and immediately put it to work in the real world — not in a spreadsheet, but scaling a YouTube channel from nothing to 300,000 followers while tracking every metric that moved the needle.</p>
      <p>Along the way I taught myself iOS and Android development and <strong>shipped a full-stack social travel app</strong> across three platforms using Swift, Kotlin, JavaScript, and Firebase. That's the kind of thing that doesn't show up on a standard finance resume — and it's exactly what makes mine different.</p>
      <p>I'm looking for a role where analytical thinking and a builder's mindset actually matter. Revenue modeling, data-driven strategy, product operations — I'm at home anywhere numbers meet execution.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="skills-list reveal" style="transition-delay:.1s">
      <div>
        <div class="skill-name">Financial Analysis &amp; Modeling</div>
        <div class="skill-bar"><div class="skill-fill" style="width:88%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="skill-name">Revenue Strategy &amp; Analytics</div>
        <div class="skill-bar"><div class="skill-fill" style="width:92%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="skill-name">Content &amp; Audience Growth</div>
        <div class="skill-bar"><div class="skill-fill" style="width:95%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="skill-name">Mobile &amp; Full-Stack Dev</div>
        <div class="skill-bar"><div class="skill-fill" style="width:70%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="skill-name">Swift / Kotlin / JavaScript</div>
        <div class="skill-bar"><div class="skill-fill" style="width:68%"></div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="skill-name">Data-Driven Decision Making</div>
        <div class="skill-bar"><div class="skill-fill" style="width:88%"></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="work" style="background:var(--paper)">
  <div class="section-label"><span>Experience</span></div>
  <h2 class="section-title reveal">Where I've <em>made</em> things happen</h2>
  <div>
    <div class="work-item reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="work-company">Otto Kilcher</div>
        <div class="work-period">Mar 2024 — Present</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="work-role">Revenue Analyst &amp; Content Producer</div>
        <p class="work-p">Sole operator of YouTube and Facebook growth strategy for Otto Kilcher — Alaskan homesteader and cast member of Discovery Channel's Alaska: The Last Frontier. Grew both platforms from zero to 300,000+ followers and generated over $50,000 in channel revenue through data-driven content strategy and production.</p>
        <p class="work-p">Analyzed audience retention, engagement signals, and monetization metrics to inform every production decision. Built scalable workflows that increased output while operating independently with minimal resources.</p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag hi">$50K+ revenue</span>
          <span class="tag hi">300K+ followers</span>
          <span class="tag hi">2M peak views</span>
          <span class="tag">Performance Analytics</span>
          <span class="tag">YouTube SEO</span>
          <span class="tag">Content Strategy</span>
          <span class="tag">Monetization Modeling</span>
          <span class="tag">Video Production</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="work-item reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="work-company">TravelBroche</div>
        <div class="work-period">Dec 2023 — Present</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="work-role">Founder &amp; Full-Stack Developer</div>
        <p class="work-p">Independently designed and built a full-stack social travel mobile application — from concept to deployed product. Built for iOS (Swift/Xcode) and Android (Kotlin), with a web interface in JavaScript and a complete Firebase backend including real-time database and user authentication.</p>
        <p class="work-p">Managed the complete product lifecycle: UX decisions, architecture, technical implementation, and iteration. Demonstrates the ability to self-direct, learn new skills fast, and ship.</p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag hi">Shipped solo</span>
          <span class="tag">Swift / Xcode</span>
          <span class="tag">Kotlin</span>
          <span class="tag">JavaScript</span>
          <span class="tag">Firebase</span>
          <span class="tag">Real-time DB</span>
          <span class="tag">User Auth</span>
          <span class="tag">iOS &amp; Android</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

